her quest for equipment. My research on this phenomenon was concluded when I accessed message boards on items from Vex Thal. It seems that no matter how uber an item gets, uberitis affects the part of the brain which is satisfied, and thus makes the item seem unworthy of the effort needed to attain it. The best item in EverQuest simply *isn't good enough*. I stress this, because it leads into a dire and foreboding theory.<br><br>Eventually, the vast majority of players will be at the required level to catch uberitis. At this point you will simply have a majority of unsatisfied people. Those satisfied with the game will become outnumbered and leave. More people who aren't satisfied will leave too, as the game becomes less important. Left alone, this would simply continue until all the uberfied people leave, and new players eventually regain control. This will not remain unchecked. Verant will see the declining profitability of EverQuest. What happens from there is anyone's guess, but it would appear obvious.<br><br>And so my first Prophecy is born: Uberitis will cause the demise of EQ. Unless something more appealing is revealed in the future, it would appear that we may all be forcefully cured of our addiction.<br><br>*Note: Please be offended by my post. It was my intention. My email is included for your convenience.<br><br><br>Ares out.<br><br>Indasha - aresprophet@hotmail.com<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/upyrastilia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pyrastilia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 421<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/30/02 3:29:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3447.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> I fail to see how anyone would find your post o