 this arena.<br><br>Actually, I used to spend 10+ hours a day in EQ roleplaying... but I won't say it went defunct, I just lost interest in what was left of it. So I figured 'hell, I might as level up to 60 and see if anyone could use me'. So, I threw out a few apps, and got a response from the newly reformed Magister. When I raided with them, I wasn't thinking 'lootlootlootloot', I was thinking this was pretty fun. Organized butt stompings, as opposed to the messes I had been in before.<br><br>If this conditioned really existed, Magister and Midnight Fury would still be raping NToV for the pretty much free loot that just drops in waves there.<br><br>Now if you want to whine, bitch, moan and judge, go ahead, this board caters specifically to those desires. Just don't assume that everyone is driven by loot like you are, but they might be actually enjoying a part of the game that you don't. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uskerrynb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SkerryNB</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/30/02 7:14:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3447.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hrm.</span><hr size=1> Well, like Pyrastillia said,  prophets like yourself were coming up with this vision of MMORPG Rapture long before now.<br><br><br>And as with all of them, likewise will yours fall into oblivion.<br><br><br>MMORPGS have a strange, very strange phenom around them.  They don't die. Even the ones that started off absolutly horrible.  They don't die.<br><br>Yes, maybe you and 200 other folks will leave,  but there will be plenty of others coming in to take their place.<br><br>Hell, last I knew WW2 Online was still going. . <br><br>They just don't die. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uindashasilvervine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Indasha Silvervine</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 83<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/1/02 12:44:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3447.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> point</span><hr size=1> You fail to see the point in my post.<br><br>It would appear that few of you have been exposed to Satire. This, while an amateur attempt, falls into that category (I cannot compete with professionals). Still, the general tone exists. Glad that's out of the way.<br><br>I don't claim to have new ideas. I don't claim to see things in a new light. Look at my email address. Note the word Prophet. Maybe instead of immediately criticizing, you could attempt to appreciate. Or it that unknown to most of you as well?<br><br>How is this offensive? It is aimed at the uber people who complain about loot. My point is that they are ruining the game. I refer to uberness as a disease, after all. So, such uber people (should they find time to read my humble post), may take offense.<br><br>If you can honestly say you play the game simply for the friends and the fun, then you sir are a truly excellent person. And inferring that I play for the loot is uncalled for. Again, I'm satirizing that. I figured the little disclaimer at the top might clue some people in. At any rate, there is a serious issue at hand, one that needs to be considered. Stuff can only get so uber with the stat caps, haste caps, what have you. Then you have unsatisfied people. With a game as old as EQ, that's a lot of players. Should they decide to leave because the